00:10:01.960 --> 00:10:08.280
What this means on the Posit Connect side is that if I'm a developer and I'm building some

00:10:08.280 --> 00:10:12.679
sort of a dashboard, and this dashboard is built on top of some data inside of Snowflake,

00:10:12.679 --> 00:10:17.159
and then I want to share this dashboard with my company or my department or whoever it might be,

00:10:18.119 --> 00:10:23.320
a common thing that we've seen is that in many cases, there are very granular permissions

00:10:23.320 --> 00:10:28.840
defined on that data. So-and-so can see this slice of the data, so-and-so can see this slice

00:10:28.840 --> 00:10:34.599
of the data, but there's requirements or there's regulations that prohibit user A from seeing the

00:10:34.599 --> 00:10:40.200
