00:10:40.200 --> 00:10:48.599
building business critical or business analytics type applications. Because historically, we've

00:10:48.599 --> 00:10:53.640
relied on things like service accounts to give us a shared access into the underlying data.

00:10:53.640 --> 00:10:59.479
But then how do we take that service account and create an even narrower scope for the specific

00:10:59.479 --> 00:11:03.880
user who happens to be viewing the application at a specific point in time? And I've seen all

00:11:03.880 --> 00:11:09.320
kinds of creative and clever solutions that we feel good about, but security doesn't. And we

